### 4. Dynamic Elements (Incidents, Events, Changes) ###

# Event Records
<https://w3id.org/noria/event/DB_Down_Log_20240423_0900>
    a noria:EventRecord ;
    rdfs:label "Database Server Down Log Entry"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Log entry indicating that the production database server became unreachable."@en ;
    noria:loggingTime "2024-04-23T09:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    noria:logOriginatingManagedObject <https://w3id.org/noria/resource/DB_Server_01> ;
    noria:logOriginatingManagementSystem <https://w3id.org/noria/application/Monitoring_System> ;
    noria:logText "CRITICAL: Database server db01.prod.example.com is down. No response to ping."@en ;
    noria:alarmSeverity <Notification/Severity/PerceivedSeverity/Critical_extra_node_1> ;
    .

<https://w3id.org/noria/event/Interface_Down_Log_20240423_0905>
    a noria:EventRecord ;
    rdfs:label "Router_extra_node_1 Interface Down Log Entry"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Log entry indicating a network interface on the core router went down, potentially related to DB server issue."@en ;
